this code will cause "nested sleeping primitives" issue which are turning up on systems running the 3.19-rc kernels... because now you're porting it to 4.4 kernel version. 

see these link for references:
https://lwn.net/Articles/628628/ 
https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/virtualization/2015-February/029369.html 

Eventually, we will see the kernel warning log like this: 
 --- do not call blocking ops when !TASK_RUNNING; state=1 ....

for bug fix, refer to :
https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/virtualization/2015-February/029392.html
http://article.gmane.org/gmane.linux.kernel.virtualization/24851

